    <div class="font-body-math text-xl bg-surface-container-low text-on-surface p-4 rounded-lg border border-outline-variant/20 flex flex-col items-center gap-3">
    <p class="">\nabla \cdot \mathbf{F} = \frac{\partial}{\partial x}(x) + \frac{\partial}{\partial y}(y) + \frac{\partial}{\partial z}(z)</p>
    <div class="h-px w-12 bg-outline-variant/30"></div>
    <p class="">\nabla \cdot \mathbf{F} = 1 + 1 + 1 = <span class="text-secondary font-bold">3</span></p>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-on-surface-variant font-body-ui text-sm leading-relaxed italic">By calculating the divergence of the field, we determine the density of the source at each point.</p>
